===========================================================================================================================
1. Effect
Purpose: Tells whether the policy allows or denies the specified actions.

Values:

"Allow" ‚Äì Grants permission.

"Deny" ‚Äì Explicitly blocks permission (even if another policy allows it).

‚úÖ 2. Action
Purpose: Specifies what operations are permitted or denied.

Format: "service:action" (or "service:*" for all actions in that service).

Example:

"s3:GetObject" ‚Äì Allows reading an object from an S3 bucket.

"s3:*" ‚Äì Allows all actions in S3.

"ec2:StartInstances" ‚Äì Allows starting EC2 instances.

‚úÖ 3. Resource
Purpose: Specifies which AWS resources the actions apply to.

Format: Usually an ARN (Amazon Resource Name) or "*" for all resources.

Examples:

"*" ‚Äì All S3 buckets, all EC2 instances, etc.

"arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket" ‚Äì A specific S3 bucket.

"arn:aws:ec2:us-east-1:123456789012:instance/i-1234567890abcdef0" ‚Äì A specific EC2 instance.

